  "text": "The simulation started with 2 = 0.012 but this was reduced with each of the five loops of five cycles down to 2 = 0 for the last loop. The slow decrease in 2 allowed a better chance of the best fit being found [CITATION_1] . Fig. 11 shows the observed and calculated PDFs over the two ranges used in the fittings. The models show good agreement with the data. For the fit range of 1.75 < r < 20.0 Å the final 2 was 0.0026, and 2 = 0.00063 when the fit was restricted to 1.75 < r < 8 Å .",
